<%# JSON-LD schemas %>
<%= breadcrumb_schema([
  { name: "Home", url: root_url },
  { name: "Suites", url: nil },
  { name: "Home Buying Suite" }
]) %>

<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "What is a home buying calculator suite?", answer: "A home buying calculator suite is a guided workflow that walks you through the essential financial calculations for purchasing a home, step by step. Each calculator builds on the previous one so you get a complete picture of your home buying budget." },
  { question: "How much house can I afford?", answer: "How much house you can afford depends on your annual income, existing monthly debts, available down payment, and current mortgage rates. A common guideline is that your total housing costs should not exceed 28% of your gross monthly income." },
  { question: "Should I rent or buy a home?", answer: "The rent vs buy decision depends on how long you plan to stay, local housing costs, mortgage rates, and your financial goals. Generally, buying makes more sense if you plan to stay at least 5-7 years, while renting offers more flexibility for shorter time horizons." },
  { question: "What order should I use these calculators?", answer: "Start with the Home Affordability Calculator to determine your maximum budget, then use the Mortgage Calculator to see monthly payments for different loan terms, and finally compare renting vs buying with the Rent vs Buy Calculator to confirm that purchasing makes financial sense." }
]) %>

<%# Breadcrumbs %>
<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", items: [
  { name: "Home", url: root_path },
  { name: "Suites" },
  { name: "Home Buying Suite" }
] %>

<div class="mb-10">
  <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Home Buying Calculator Suite</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-3xl">Work through the complete home buying process step by step. Each calculator feeds into the next to give you a complete financial picture.</p>
</div>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %>

<div class="mt-8 space-y-6" data-controller="suite-stepper">
  <%# Step 1: Home Affordability %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-indigo-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">1</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-blue-600 dark:group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">How Much Can You Afford?</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Calculate your maximum home price based on income and debts</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Start by determining how much home you can afford based on your annual income, monthly debts, and available down payment.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Home Affordability Calculator", finance_home_affordability_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-indigo-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 2: Mortgage %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-indigo-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">2</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-blue-600 dark:group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Calculate Monthly Payments</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">See your monthly mortgage payment, total interest, and amortization</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Enter the home price and down payment from Step 1 to calculate your monthly mortgage payments.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Mortgage Calculator", finance_mortgage_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-indigo-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 3: Rent vs Buy %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-indigo-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">3</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-blue-600 dark:group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Rent vs Buy Analysis</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Compare the long-term costs of renting vs buying</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Use your mortgage payment from Step 2 to compare renting vs buying over time.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Rent vs Buy Calculator", finance_rent_vs_buy_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-indigo-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %>

<article class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none mt-12">
  <h2>How to Use the Home Buying Calculator Suite</h2>
  <p>Buying a home is one of the biggest financial decisions you'll make. This calculator suite guides you through the essential calculations in the right order, so each step builds on the previous one.</p>

  <h3>Step-by-Step Guide</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Determine affordability</strong> -- Start with your income and debts to find your maximum budget.</li>
    <li><strong>Calculate mortgage payments</strong> -- Use your budget to compare different loan terms and rates.</li>
    <li><strong>Compare renting vs buying</strong> -- Make sure buying makes financial sense for your situation.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Why Use a Calculator Suite?</h3>
  <p>Individual calculators are great for quick answers, but the home buying process involves multiple interconnected decisions. Your affordability determines your loan amount, which determines your monthly payment, which determines whether buying beats renting. By working through these steps in order, you avoid the common mistake of looking at homes outside your true budget.</p>

  <h3>Tips for Accurate Results</h3>
  <p>For the most accurate results, gather your financial documents before starting. You will need your annual gross income, current monthly debt payments (car loans, student loans, credit cards), estimated down payment amount, and a rough idea of current mortgage rates in your area. Having these numbers ready lets you move through the suite quickly and get realistic results.</p>
</article>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "multiplex" %>
